CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 12, 1954, pg. 4, reads: "Pitt Graduation - These young men and women were among the 1561 who were granted degrees Wednesday at the spring commencement of the University of Pittsburgh. They are, left to right:...Charles B. McNutt and Willa C. White, both of whom were honor graduates in School of Education....-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of University of Pittsburgh School of Education graduates Charles B. McNutt and Willa C. White, posed in Cathedral of Learning
